Sentencas: New Sr0.5Bi0.5FeO3-delta (SBF) and Sr0.5Bi0.45FeO3-delta(SB0.45F) oxides are systematically investigated as oxygen reduction cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: The SBF and SB0.45F samples have been discovered that form single-phase solid solutions while maintaining outstanding chemical stability with gadolinium-doped ceria (Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95, GDC) even sintering at 1000 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficients (TECs) for SBF and SB0.45F are very similar to the electrolyte of GDC.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: XPS and iodometric titration results reveal that A-site deficient SB0.45F cathode possesses a high oxygen vacancy concentration, which can greatly enhance the electrochemical performance of porous cathode.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: A low polarization resistance (R (p)) is shown for the SB0.45F cathode based on a symmetrical cell test, obtained by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: Additionally, the deconvolution results of the EIS test display that the ORR rate of the SB0.45F cathode should be jointly limited by the charge transfer processes and oxygen adsorption processes.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: The peak power output of a single solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) equipped with the SB0.45F cathode reaches 0.77 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, about 1.75 times of SBF.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies

Sentencas: These findings suggest that the Bi-deficient SB0.45F perovskite oxide is an outstanding catalyst for IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Highly Improved Electrochemical Performance of a Fe-based Cathode by Introducing A-site Cationic Deficiencies
